items.title: Parle Biscuits FY24 Results: Profit surges two-fold, revenue rises 2%
items.description: Parle Biscuits posted a revenue of Rs 15,086 crore for FY 2023-24, with a net profit of Rs 1,607 crore, marking a 115% increase from the previous year. The company noted an increase in advertising and promotional expenses by 3.23%. FMCG firms expect demand revival amid inflation-led price hikes.

items.title: Headwinds stir, but fail to shake as ET500 companies show strong revenue and profit growth in FY24
items.description: On a year-on-year basis, the sample's revenue increased by 8.7% in FY24, slower than the 22% growth in the previous year, reflecting demand weakness. Net profit, on the other hand, shot up by 30% to Rs 14.2 lakh crore due to softer input costs and stable interest outgo relative to the operating profit (EBIT). Net margin improved to 8.7% compared with 7.3% in the previous year and 4.9% five years ago.
